        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 3:24PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>At 323 PM MDT, the public reported a strong thunderstorm near Kit
Carson, or 22 miles west of Cheyenne Wells, moving north at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Public.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of north central
Cheyenne County in east central Colorado.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
